hands_on_practices.problem:
A continuous-time signal, denoted by $x(t)$, is described by the following piecewise function:
$$
x(t) = \begin{cases}
\frac{t}{2} & \text{for } 0 \le t \le 2 \\
2 - \frac{t}{2} & \text{for } 2 < t \le 4 \\
0 & \text{otherwise}
\end{cases}
$$
Any continuous-time signal can be expressed as the sum of its even and odd components, $x(t) = x_e(t) + x_o(t)$. The even component, $x_e(t)$, is defined by the relation $x_e(t) = \frac{1}{2}[x(t) + x(-t)]$.

Calculate the value of the even component $x_e(t)$ at the specific time $t = -3$. Provide your answer as a single real number, either as a decimal or a fraction.
